ok type as ur search box this : http://192.168.0.1
user:admin
pass: (leave it blank)
you are now on site
click advanced.
then after that you see all kinds of stuff to fill in… put this

enable-
name- (anything)
private ip:
for this you will need to press start-run-cmd-type “ipconfig”, then your ip adress is your priavte ip
proto type: tcp
public port: 43594
private port: 43594
always on
